.TH "device_offline" 9 "device_offline" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_offline \- Prepare the device for hot-removal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" device_offline
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to be put offline.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Execute the device bus type's .\fBoffline\fP callback, if present, to prepare
the device for a subsequent hot-removal.  If that succeeds, the device must
not be used until either it is removed or its bus type's .\fBonline\fP callback
is executed.

Call under device_hotplug_lock.
